### Updating User Attributes

Sometimes, users may want to update their information, such as their email address or other attributes. To facilitate this, we can create a function in our `auth.js` helper file to update user attributes.

<Instruction>Add the following code to the `auth.js` file to implement the `updateUserAttributes` function:</Instruction>

```js
export function updateUserAttributes(attributesToUpdate) {
  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
    const cognitoUser = userPool.getCurrentUser()

    if (cognitoUser) {
      cognitoUser.getSession((err, session) => {
        if (err) {
          reject(err)
          return
        }

        const attributeList = Object.entries(attributesToUpdate).map(
          ([Name, Value]) => new CognitoUserAttribute({ Name, Value })
        )

        cognitoUser.updateAttributes(attributeList, (err, result) => {
          if (err) {
            reject(err)
            return
          }
          resolve(result)
        })
      })
    } else {
      reject(new Error("No user found"))
    }
  })
}
```

The `updateUserAttributes` function takes an object with the attributes to update. It checks if there's a currently authenticated user and, if so, updates the user's attributes in Cognito. If there's no authenticated user, it rejects the promise with an error.

